sub_title: Senior Investigator at International Rescue Committee
summary:
I have led fact-finding missions in Burkina Faso, Burundi, Côte d’Ivoire, the Democratic Republic of Congo, Djibouti, Ethiopia, Mali, Nigeria, Rwanda, South Sudan, Tanzania, Togo, Uganda and the UAE.

From 2012 to 2015, I served on three occasions as an expert on the United Nations Group of Experts on the Democratic Republic of the Congo and in December 2012 I was appointed by the UN Secretary General as the Group’s Coordinator.
